Hi! Im Sita Pataballa, and I normally go by Sita.


I’m a huge foodie that enjoys a mostly street food, but likes to try the variety of foods from all cultures. I also really love some nice fashion(Costume related) content.


My interest in web development started when I was 23 years old and began to try desiginig some web applications using HTML CSS as a practice. I wanted to be the most hands on as a business owner, and make sure that my vision wasn’t tainted by the views of anyone else. Cue my descent into web development. I spent a whole day pouring over my website, using HTML and CSS, not really having a clue what I was doing, but loving every second of it. In the end, I was so excited when people asked me who built my professional website, and I without hesitation could proudly say myself. Fast-forward to today, and I have had the privilege of honing my skills by graduating a software immersive, that really helped to develop my skills so that I can write clean, scalable code, that is also user friendly.
